Pupil Detection

Fixed up image in GIMP

clear;close all; clc;
input_img = imread('pupil1_fixed.png');
img_gray = rgb2gray(input_img);
figure;
imshow(img_gray)
title('Grayscale Image')
edges = detect_edges(double(img_gray));
figure;
imshow(edges)
title('Edges of Image')
[Y,X,R] = detect_circles(edges);
theta = 0:pi/50:2*pi;
y = R*sin(theta)+Y;
x = R*cos(theta)+X;
figure; hold on;
imshow(img_gray);
plot(x,y,'LineWidth',3);
title('Grayscale Image with Circle Annotation')
hold off;

Check performance of Sobel Filter on RGB image

clear;close all; clc;
input_img = imread('pupil1.jpg');
input_edges = detect_edges(double(input_img));
img_gray = rgb2gray(input_img);
gray_edges = detect_edges(double(img_gray));
figure;
subplot(2,2,1)
imshow(input_img)
title('Input Image')
subplot(2,2,2)
imshow(img_gray)
title('Grayscale')
subplot(2,2,3)
imshow(input_edges)
title('Edges of Input Image')
subplot(2,2,4)
imshow(gray_edges)
title('Edges of Grayscale')
Looking at the result, there appears to be something odd happening with how the edges are defined for the Input (RGB) image.

Sobel Filter

function edges = detect_edges(A)
%this function returns the edges of the input
% grayscale image `A`
% Sobel operation
Gx = [-1,0,1;-2,0,2;-1,0,1];
Gy = [-1,-2,-1;0,0,0;1,2,1];
% declare matrices for info storage
[rows, cols] = size(A);
mag = zeros(size(A));
% dir = zeros(size(A));
% convolve Gx and Gy over A
for ii = 1:rows-2
for jj = 1:cols-2
Sx = sum(Gx.*A(ii:ii+2,jj:jj+2),'all');
Sy = sum(Gy.*A(ii:ii+2,jj:jj+2),'all');
mag(ii+1,jj+1) = sqrt(Sx.^2 + Sy.^2);
% dir(ii+1,jj+1) = int32(atan(Sy/Sx)*180/pi);
end
end
% Thresholding
% declare threshold - differs by application
threshold = mean(mag,'all');
threshold = threshold*3.2;
% enforce threshold
edges = zeros(size(mag));
edges(mag > threshold) = 1;
end

Hough Transform

function [Y,X,R,votes] = detect_circles(edge_map)
min_radius = 10;
max_radius = 60;
[rows, cols] = size(edge_map);
% declare matrix for tracking votes for the Circle information
votes = zeros(rows,cols,max_radius);
% voting
for ii = 1:rows
for jj = 1:cols
if edge_map(ii,jj) == 1
for r = min_radius:max_radius
% sweep through phi degrees
for degrees = 1:360
% generate coordinates of circle about (jj,ii)
x = jj - int32(r*cos(degrees*pi/180));
y = ii - int32(r*sin(degrees*pi/180));
if (x+r >= cols) || (x-r < 0) || (y+r >= rows) || (y-r < 0)
continue;
end
if (x < cols) && (x > 0) && (y < rows) && (y > 0)
votes(y,x,r) = votes(y,x,r) + 1;
end
end
end
end
end
end
% get location of best circle
Y=0;X=0;R=0;V=0;
for ii = 1:rows
for jj = 1:cols
for kk = min_radius:max_radius
if votes(ii,jj,kk) > V
V = votes(ii,jj,kk);
Y = ii;
X = jj;
R = kk;
end
end
end
end
% return
end
